    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Describes motion picture film that is 35 millimeters wide with four perforations per frame on each side and having 16 frames per foot. It has been used as the standard gauge of film for professional cinematography since the earliest days of cinema.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
